    <div class="method-block">
      <h3>METHODOLOGY</h3>
      <div class="method-beats">
        <div class="method-beat">
          <span class="beat-marker">01</span>
          <p>
            <strong>Φ_S (settlement pressure)</strong> is the engine's primary signal. It measures unrealized
            settlement energy accumulating in a specific entity's field — the gap between what the system
            shows and what is currently priced or regulated. Formula derivation from Kirandeep's Law of
            Emergence: <code>E = ΔI / A</code>, where <em>ΔI</em> is information differential and <em>A</em>
            is action cost. Φ_S is the <em>ΔI</em> component measured at entity granularity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-beat">
          <span class="beat-marker">02</span>
          <p>
            <strong>Direction signal</strong> is generated at measurement time, before any outcome is known:
            Φ_S ≥ 8.0 → CRITICAL; ≥ 3.0 → BUILDING; ≥ 0.5 → ELEVATED; &lt; 0.5 → LOW. The prediction window
            is 30 days.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-beat">
          <span class="beat-marker">03</span>
          <p>
            <strong>Accuracy assessment</strong> — where a subsequent reading for the same entity exists
            within the window: if BUILDING/ELEVATED and pressure held or rose → CONFIRMED. If LOW and no
            subsequent escalation → CONFIRMED_QUIET. Accuracy rate counts confirmed outcomes over all
            assessable signals (excludes PENDING and infra-scale).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-beat">
          <span class="beat-marker">04</span>
          <p>
            <strong>Infrastructure-scale entities</strong> (Ethereum, Base, Coinbase) measure total cumulative
            flow volume — a different dimensional unit from field-level pressure. These are logged but
            excluded from accuracy calculation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-beat">
          <span class="beat-marker">05</span>
          <p>
            <strong>On-chain verification</strong> — system state is periodically committed to Base mainnet
            via the GeniusFlow Settlement Contract. Each commitment includes a SHA-256 proof hash of the
            engine state at time of claim.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

